items.title: Tariffs are expected to start showing up more in consumer prices as holiday shopping season starts
items.description: Impacts have been muted so far as companies built up inventories ahead of the duties and have absorbed some of the impact.

items.title: Trump cuts fentanyl tariffs on China to 10% as Beijing delays latest rare earths curbs by a year
items.description: Trump said he will be going to China in April, followed by a trip by Xi to the U.S. without specifying a timeline.

items.title: European Central Bank holds rates steady as economy shows resilience
items.description: Top ECB board members told CNBC this month that the easing cycle is close to, or at its end.

items.title: From futuristic NEOM to tech and tourism, Saudi Arabia's priorities are shifting
items.description: Saudi's economy minister told CNBC the country was "reprioritizing a little bit towards sectors that need it the most."
